title: ANA Boeing 777 makes emergency landing due to engine trouble - Travelandtourworld.comTravelandtourworld.com
text:
ANA Boeing 777 makes emergency landing due to engine trouble Published on : Wednesday, August 26, 2015
Following an engine trouble, a Boeing 777 flight operated by Japan’s All Nippon Airways (ANA) had to make an emergency landing in Osaka on Wednesday. There were 246 passengers on board the flight along with 11 crew members. The airline revealed that there were no injuries and the plane landed safely.
The ANA flight from Osaka to Tokyo left the airport at 7:18 am (2218 GMT, Tuesday), but the crew soon identified a problem with the engine and the pilot requested an emergency landing. The plane landed back at Osaka airport at 7:50 am.
According to the reports, the passengers were taken evacuated safely from the airplane after the emergency landing.
The airline is investigating the incident which reports that the pilots encountered power output problems with the left engine and abnormal temperatures in the engine’s emissions.
